result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (6th) [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Conc. (.17-.199)] and Operating w/ PAC (5th) [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Conc. (.17-.199)]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (6th) [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Conc. (.17-.199)] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th) [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Conc. (.17-.199)] was dismissed by the court.

  • Jeffery A. Hanson was found guilty of OWI (6th) [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Conc. (.17-.199)], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in court with attorney Linda J Schaefer.  Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in custody.  Joan M Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Minute sheet. State amends Ct. 1 to OWI 6th, gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters guilty plea to Ct. 1 as amended.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty of amended Ct. 1, OWI 6th. Court dismisses Cts. 2, 3 & 4 but reads in for sentencing. Court reviews collateral consequences, possible penalties for felony conviction with defendant. Defendant must have a DNA sample on file with the State of Wisconsin. Court orders PSI. Bond remains in effect.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 5, 2014 at 11:00 am.
Defense waives reading of Information and enters not guilty plea.  Bond remains as is.

Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in court with attorney Linda J Schaefer.  Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in custody.  Joan M Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense waives right to Prelim. Court questions defendant on waiver. Court finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver and binds over for trial. Court finds probable cause for bindover.  Status conference scheduled for June 30, 2014 at 08:15 am.

State requests an additional $1,000 cash bond because of the non-appearance yesterday and new charges pending. Atty Korb makes statement. Atty Schaefer gives argument, asks court to consider a lower cash bond. Court makes statement, not changing bond in this file, sets larger cash bond on new charges.

Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in court with attorney Linda J Schaefer.  Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in custody.  Joan M Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file, quashes warrant. Defense waives reading of the complaint, asks court to set matter for a status conference, needs time to discuss preliminary hearing with defendant. Defense does waive time limit for prelim. Status set.
Defendant in custody.  Status conference scheduled for May 22, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Linda J Schaefer in court.  Raymond L Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. Atty Schaefer advises defendant knew about todays hearing, not sure where defendant is this morning, may have had transportation issues. State requests bench warrant. Court orders bench warrant but stays signing it until noon to allow Atty Schaefer time to locate defendant and make other arrangements for him to appear.

Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in court.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Copy of Complaint given to Defendant in Court.  Court reviews charge(s), max. penalties, right to counsel, right to preliminary hearing. Defendant indicates Atty Linda Schaefer will be representing him, not sure why she's not here. Court questions defendant whether he contacted PD office to have Atty Schaefer appointed to this case. Defendant hasn't talked to PD office re: this case. Court advises defendant to go talk to Atty Maciolek and then return. Defendant returns with Atty Maciolek. Defendant does qualify for PD representation, Atty Maciolek hoping that Atty Schaefer will take PD appointment on this case also. Court reschedules. Bond remains in effect. AIA 4/21/14 at 10:00 AM.

$955 cash transferred from resident funds to be applied toward cash bond. Defendant paid the remaining $545 by credit card. As of 4/04/14, credit card monies have not been deposited in the Clerk of Courts account.
Defendant was fingerprinted 3/29/14 by jail staff. (fingerprint card destroyed 9/15/14)
Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol.  Do not operate a motor vehicle without a valid drivers license and subject to any conditions or restrictions on that license.

Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson appears by video conference.  Raymond L. Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State gives incident report, potential charges. Court questions Defendant on address/employment history, reviews right to Counsel. Court finds probable cause, sets bond.  Initial appearance scheduled for April 7, 2014 at 10:00 am.
